20 WHEREAS, Arkansas State Game and Fish Commission Game Warden Brady
21 Smith earned the National Wild Turkey Federation's Wildlife Officer of the
22 Year Award at the forty-ninth annual National Wild Turkey Federation
23 Convention and Sport Show held on February 14, 2025; and
24
25 WHEREAS, the Wildlife Officer of the Year Award is given to individuals
26 who have excelled and demonstrated exceptional performance in teamwork and
27 innovation, attitude and leadership, and achievements and accomplishments;
28 and
29
30 WHEREAS, while this award is usually akin to a lifetime achievement
31 award, Game Warden Smith earned this award in only his second year as an
32 Arkansas State Game and Fish Commission Game Warden; and
33
34 WHEREAS, Game Warden Smith works in Cleburne County, which is one of
35 Arkansas's busiest counties for game wardens during hunting seasons, and he
36 also assists neighboring counties in their efforts to curtail poaching
